# Expense Tracker API

A REST API for tracking personal expenses with user authentication.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js + Express
- MySQL
- JWT Authentication
- bcrypt password hashing

## Setup

1. Clone the repo
2. Install dependencies:
   npm install

3. Create a .env file:
   PORT=3000
   DB_HOST=localhost
   DB_USER=expense_user
   DB_PASSWORD=expense123
   DB_NAME=expense_tracker
   JWT_SECRET=mysecretkey123

4. Create MySQL database and tables (see schema below)
5. Run the server:
   npm run dev

## API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | /auth/signup | Register new user |
| POST | /auth/login | Login and get JWT token |

### Expenses (JWT required)
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | /expenses | Get all expenses |
| GET | /expenses?range=week | Filter by past week |
| GET | /expenses?range=month | Filter by past month |
| GET | /expenses?range=3months | Filter by past 3 months |
| GET | /expenses?start=YYYY-MM-DD&end=YYYY-MM-DD | Custom date range |
| POST | /expenses | Add new expense |
| PUT | /expenses/:id | Update expense |
| DELETE | /expenses/:id | Delete expense |

## Expense Categories
Groceries, Leisure, Electronics, Utilities, Clothing, Health, Others